<body>
    <h1>Katrisk Documents</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>KATRISK Workflow</p>
<ol>
<li>Since we don=E2=80=99t get Katrisk Exposure data currently, we will rel=
y on the EDM to Katrisk converter for now.</li>
<li>We first need to attach the EDM to SQL server clv435pw-540123, which is=
 the Risk Link database.</li>
<li>After that we can convert EDM using the Command Prompt. The detailed pr=
ocess is given here: "Y:\Katrisk\EDM_Conversion_1.3\EDM to SpatialKat Expos=
ure Conversion.docx". Note that you can convert Exposure for only 1 peril b=
y default and the Peril value is set to 3 in katrisk by default.(Peril valu=
e 3 =3D Flood)</li>
<li>You can find the converted .csv files in the location specified by you =
while converting in Demand Prompt.</li>
</ol>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"102" src=3D"5c04f216dc2212c7e25a9d8ace98e375" data-image-src=3D"/downl=
oad/attachments/450761411/image2021-7-30_17-33-38.png?version=3D1&amp;modif=
icationDate=3D1627646618000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"=
0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"452072564" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1"=
 data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alia=
s=3D"image2021-7-30_17-33-38.png" data-base-url=3D"https://pimcowiki.pimco.=
imswest.sscims.com" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-li=
nked-resource-container-id=3D"450761411" data-linked-resource-container-ver=
sion=3D"2" width=3D"379"></span></p>
<p>Import the converted .csv Files to Spatialkat. <strong>Make sure that th=
e LOB is same for all locations of a single account</strong>. You can impor=
t the data in Spatial Kat by going to Exposure &gt; Import Exposure &gt; Se=
lect the location and other .csv files that you got as an output from Conve=
rter.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"a5854725f36ca717156563229051be=
8a" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/450761411/image2021-7-30_17-33-=
55.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1627646635000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-=
unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"452072565" data-l=
inked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-=
linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-7-30_17-33-55.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://pimcowiki.pimco.imswest.sscims.com" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"450761411" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"2" width=3D"468" height=3D"234"></span>=
</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"6d18f8d493449e86ec6d149da67a6d=
d0" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/450761411/image2021-7-30_17-36-=
2.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1627646763000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-u=
nresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"452072566" data-li=
nked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-l=
inked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-7-30_17-36-2.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://pimcowiki.pimco.imswest.sscims.com" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"450761411" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"2" width=3D"304" height=3D"356"></span>=
</p>
<p>After the import is complete you can find the imported Exposure data in =
the Katrisk remote machine (clv435pw-16fdf4). There will be an ExposureID m=
entioned after import is complete on UI. Eg. 3180e38e-594f-4f9b-b99b-c00ef7=
c6153c. In this case the imported Exposure data will be saved here: E:\Spat=
ialKat.4.0.0.0.NA\Input_Output\exposure\PIMCO\3180e38e-594f-4f9b-b99b-c00ef=
7c6153c. You can ignore the Binary files, and copy the .csv file to Y:\ so =
that you can open the .csv files in Excel on PIMCO machines.</p>
<p>Another way is to click on the download button and select the Exposure. =
A zip folder containing the .csv files will be downloaded.</p>
<p>The Next tab is of Analysis <strong>Profile</strong>. This tab contains =
list of all the Analysis settings created by us. Analysis settings are set =
of settings/configuration that you want to select while running any analysi=
s. It is analogous to the Template that we select in AIR. You can create ne=
w Analysis profile in this tab.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"38e85b1644daae593e79345b63e6f8=
cc" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/450761411/image2021-7-30_17-37-=
49.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1627646869000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-=
unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"452072569" data-l=
inked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-=
linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-7-30_17-37-49.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://pimcowiki.pimco.imswest.sscims.com" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"450761411" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"2" width=3D"468" height=3D"109"></span>=
</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"ec4bf002c350ba7740d11ce78d9cbe=
c1" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/450761411/image2021-7-30_17-38-=
7.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1627646887000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-u=
nresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"452072570" data-li=
nked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-l=
inked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-7-30_17-38-7.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://pimcowiki.pimco.imswest.sscims.com" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"450761411" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"2" width=3D"267" height=3D"361"></span>=
</p>
<p>Add a new Analysis profile Window</p>
<p>Now you can run analysis on the Exposure that was imported. To do that g=
o to the Analysis &gt; ModelRun in SpatialKat. Select the Exposure and the =
analysis setting that you want to choose to run the analysis. The analysis =
will start to run.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"d69d1d147812517352b9650b3f70f5=
26" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/450761411/image2021-7-30_17-39-=
0.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1627646940000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-u=
nresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"452072571" data-li=
nked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-l=
inked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-7-30_17-39-0.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://pimcowiki.pimco.imswest.sscims.com" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"450761411" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"2" width=3D"468" height=3D"160"></span>=
</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"f015cb1b82ce97c4ad4aa8631a55bc=
e6" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/450761411/image2021-7-30_17-39-=
18.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1627646958000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-=
unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"452072572" data-l=
inked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-=
linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-7-30_17-39-18.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://pimcowiki.pimco.imswest.sscims.com" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"450761411" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"2" width=3D"468" height=3D"436"></span>=
</p>
<p>Once the Analysis is complete, you will be able to see the Summary of th=
e results on the UI itself. The ELT of the Analysis will be saved in the re=
mote machine. Path for the same is: E:\SpatialKat.4.0.0.0.NA\Input_Output\o=
utput\PIMCO\9260d379-e048-4ed1-967c-09c11c983876</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"804894bfaf2ad04689b41ca4a864b9=
4d" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/450761411/image2021-7-30_17-39-=
49.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1627646989000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-=
unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"452072573" data-l=
inked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-=
linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-7-30_17-39-49.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://pimcowiki.pimco.imswest.sscims.com" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"450761411" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"2" width=3D"468" height=3D"245"></span>=
</p>
<p>The ELT is in the form of Event, Year, Sample1, Sample2,=E2=80=A6, Sampl=
e10. The mean of all the sample is taken as the loss for that event. They P=
rovide Gross, Ground Up as well as net ELTs. The name of the files will be =
<a href=3D"http://elt.combined.gr" class=3D"external-link">elt.combined.gr<=
/a> for gross loss elt and similar names for other files.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Notes:</p>
<ol>
<li>The EDM to katrisk converter uses some stored procedure that are stored=
 in SpatialKat EDM converter database. Make sure that the EDM that needs to=
 be converted and Spatialkat EDM converter database are in the same server.=
</li>
<li>If there are locations that have 0 replacement value for all 4 loss typ=
es (Building, contents, BI and appurtenant) then the location won=E2=80=99t=
 get flagged for any peril.</li>
<li>Below are some of the documents relating to Katrisk
<ol>
<li>User Document : "Y:\Katrisk\SpatialKat_User_Documentation_4.26.2019.pdf=
"</li>
<li>v4 release notes : "Y:\Katrisk\SpatialKat_Release_Notes_v4.0.pdf"</li>
<li>Converter document :
<ol>
<li>"Y:\Katrisk\EDM_Conversion_1.3\EDM to SpatialKat Exposure Conversion.do=
cx"</li>
<li>"Y:\Katrisk\EDM_Conversion_1.3\EDM_Conversion_Documentation_April2020.p=
df"</li>
</ol></li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
